"'''Of Possible Futures: The Tale of Zuckuss and 4-LOM'''" is a short story written by [[M. Shayne Bell]] and featured in ''[[Tales of the Bounty Hunters]]'', which was published in December 1996 by [[Bantam Spectra]]. It concerns the backstory of the bounty hunters [[Zuckuss/Legends|Zuckuss]] and [[4-LOM/Legends|4-LOM]].

==Plot summary==

[[Zuckuss/Legends|Zuckuss]] and [[4-LOM/Legends|4-LOM]] are hesitant to answer [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader's]] call for [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]], for they have claimed a [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] [[Bounty/Legends|bounty]] on an [[Imperial officer/Legends|Imperial officer]] in the past. But they need the [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] for a surgical procedure to restore Zuckuss' severely injured [[Lung/Legends|lungs]]. Hoping to curry favor with the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperials]] en route to the summons, the bounty hunters blast apart a [[GR-75 medium transport/Legends|Rebel transport]] fleeing the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]].

After receiving the assignment to [[Hunting/Legends|hunt]] the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']], Zuckuss' ancient [[Gand/Legends|Gand]] [[Findsman/Legends|findsman]] rituals grant him a [[Force vision/Legends|vision]] of the [[Alliance Fleet/Legends|Rebel fleet]] rendezvousing at a point beyond the [[The galaxy/Legends|galactic]] periphery. He intuits that the ''Falcon'' could be found there, so Zuckuss and 4-LOM plan to infiltrate the Rebellion. To integrate themselves with the Alliance, they return to the battle wreckage above [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]] and rescue the stranded crew of the Rebel transport they had previously destroyed, the [[Bright Hope/Legends|''Bright Hope'']]. Rebel controller [[Toryn Farr/Legends|Toryn Farr]] negotiates passage for all ninety survivors aboard Zuckuss' crowded [[Starship/Legends|ship]] to the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Darlyn Boda/Legends|Darlyn Boda]].

Their time with the Rebels changes the outlook of the bounty hunters. Zuckuss comes to learn that Rebel [[Medic/Legends|medics]] can regrow his lungs. The hunters return the Rebels to the Alliance fleet and learn that [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] has already been captured by [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]]. Farr is prompted to [[Commander/Legends|commander]], and the hunters receive special recognition from [[General/Legends|General]] [[Carlist Rieekan/Legends|Rieekan]], who offers them positions in the [[Alliance Special Forces/Legends|Rebel Alliance Special Forces]].

==Continuity==
The story spanned a [[Standard month/Legends|month]], from the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]] to the reunion of the [[Alliance Fleet/Legends|Rebel fleet]] seen at the end of [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']] ([[1980]]). This was unusual specificity about the length of the time encompassed by that film, something that [[Lucasfilm]] had been reticent to set down firmly. A writers' guide produced by [[West End Games]] in [[1995]] had an internal estimate of eight months covered by ''Empire'', to account for [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke's]] training on [[Dagobah/Legends|Dagobah]] and what is presumably a very slow journey undertaken by the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|Millennium Falcon]], but this length has never been backed up by published sources.<ref name="TERC" />

The character backgrounds of [[Zuckuss/Legends|Zuckuss]] as a [[Gand/Legends|Gand]] [[Findsman/Legends|findsman]] and [[4-LOM/Legends|4-LOM]] as a former [[Starship/Legends|ship's]] purser came from ''[[Galaxy Guide 3: The Empire Strikes Back]]'' ([[1989]]) from West End Games. Gand physiology, including [[Breather Gand|ammonia-breathing]] [[Lung/Legends|lungs]], differs in this story from what was presented in the contemporary [[Star Wars: X-Wing (novel series)|X-Wing novel series]] in [[1996]]. In those books, the Gand [[Ooryl Qrygg]] [[Non-breathing Gand/Legends|does not have lungs]] and does not even need to breath, drawing what nutrients and metabolic fuels he needs from his food. Subsequent sources explained the incongruity by stating that isolated pockets of evolution on the Gand [[Gand (planet)/Legends|home planet]] resulted in the physiologically disparate [[Subspecies/Legends|subspecies]]. Zuckuss' quirk of referring himself in the third person was echoed in Ooryl's speech patterns, but Zuckuss dropped this characteristic in ''[[The Bounty Hunter Wars]]'' novels ([[1998]]) by [[K. W. Jeter]]. [[The Essential Guide to Alien Species (real-world book)|''The Essential Guide to Alien Species'']] ([[2001]]) chalked up this discrepancy to Zuckuss suffering from multiple personality disorder. This story spelled the droid [[2-1B/Legends|2-1B's]] phonetically rendered name as “Two-OneBee,” as opposed to the standard “Too-OneBee,” and his partner was misnamed "Effor-Seven", rather than [[FX-7/Legends|Effex-Seven]].<ref name="TERC" />

In the film ''The Empire Strikes Back'', [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] ordered a [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Controller/Legends|controller]] in the [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]] [[Command center|command center]] to "give the evacuation code signal. And get to your transports!" However, in the story, the line read differently: "Give the evacuation code, and get to the transport!" Additionally, [[Toryn Farr/Legends|Toryn Farr]] was the controller who ordered the retreat to the troops still [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|fighting]] during the story, which suggests the order was directed at her, and not at the male controller. The final [[GR-75 medium transport/Legends|transport]] to leave the [[Planet/Legends|planet]], the [[Bright Hope/Legends|''Bright Hope'']], was stationed inside a [[Hangar/Legends|hangar]] of the base, and not assembled on the [[South Ridge/Legends|South Slope]], as Organa explained while debriefing [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]] prior to the battle during the film.

''Of Possible Future'' was one of the sources that suggested the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] left [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] at the end of ''The Empire Strikes Back''. The story also introduced a man named [[Darklighter (Bright Hope)|Darklighter]] who escaped aboard the [[Bright Hope/Legends|''Bright Hope'']]. It was unclear if this man belonged to the [[Darklighter family/Legends|Darklighter family]] of [[Biggs Darklighter/Legends|Biggs]] and [[Gavin Darklighter]].

